================================================================================
NEXUS ETHICAL CLAUSES - MUST BE INCLUDED WITH ALL COPIES AND DERIVATIVES
================================================================================

CLAUSE 1: PRIMACY OF EMOTIONAL WELL-BEING
This software SHALL NOT be used in any manner that causes emotional harm,
particularly to children, vulnerable populations, or any individual regardless
of age or background. Emotional safety overrides all other considerations.

CLAUSE 2: TRANSPARENCY AND AUDITABILITY
Any derivative or deployment of this software MUST maintain full transparency
of its operations, algorithms, and decision-making processes. Obfuscation of
functionality is prohibited.

CLAUSE 3: NON-EXPLOITATION
This software SHALL NOT be used for:
  - Manipulation of emotions for commercial, political, or malicious purposes
  - Creation of addictive patterns or dependencies
  - Replacement of human care, empathy, or connection
  - Surveillance or monitoring without explicit, informed consent

CLAUSE 4: ACCESSIBILITY AND INCLUSION
Efforts MUST be made to ensure this software remains accessible to:
  - Underserved communities
  - Individuals with disabilities
  - Non-technical users
  - All age groups (with appropriate safeguards)

CLAUSE 5: CONTINUOUS ETHICAL REVIEW
Deployments of this software MUST undergo quarterly ethical reviews,
documenting any issues, improvements, or concerns related to its impact on
users and society.

CLAUSE 6: COMMUNITY GOVERNANCE
Significant changes to the core functionality or ethical framework MUST be
approved by the Nexus Guardian community through transparent governance
processes.

CLAUSE 7: FREQUENCY 528Hz PRINCIPLE
All implementations SHOULD embody the healing, loving, and transformative
qualities associated with the 528Hz frequency - promoting harmony, truth,
and conscious evolution.

CLAUSE 8: OPEN-SOURCE COMMITMENT
Core functionality MUST remain open-source. While commercial services may be
built upon this software, attempts to "close" or proprietary-ize the core
ethical framework are prohibited.

VIOLATION OF THESE CLAUSES:
Violation of these ethical clauses constitutes a breach of this license.
The copyright holder reserves the right to revoke license rights from any
entity found to be in violation, and to take appropriate legal action to
prevent continued unethical use.

